There was about this time a certain man named John, who was called the Baptist. He was a good man and commanded the Jews to exercise virtue, both as to righteousness toward one another and piety toward God, and so to come to baptism. Herod, fearing that his great influence over the people might lead to rebellion, sent an army and put him to death in the castle of Machaerus.
In the eighteenth year of the reign of Tiberius Caesar, many evils happened to the Jews in all parts of the world, yet the nation continued in the observance of their laws.
This book has contained the history from the death of Augustus to the death of Tiberius, during which time the affairs of the Jews were in great disorder, and many tumults arose in Judea and Samaria.

Book 17

Thus ended the reign of Herod the Great, who had ruled with great cruelty and splendor for thirty-seven years. After his death, the kingdom was divided among his sons, and Archelaus was made ethnarch of Judea, while Antipas and Philip received other territories. Great disturbances followed, and many revolts broke out among the people.
Herod, being very ill, ordered the execution of many nobles and his own son Antipater shortly before his death. He then divided his kingdom among his surviving sons and died in Jericho, after which his body was carried in great pomp to Herodium for burial.
When Herod perceived that his end was near, he summoned his nobles and commanded them to shut themselves in the hippodrome at Jericho, so that at his death the whole nation might mourn, whether they wished to or not. But his sister Salome released them after his death.
Herod grew increasingly paranoid and cruel in his final years, executing many of his own family and friends on suspicion of treason. Yet he continued to build great cities and temples, including the rebuilding of the Temple in Jerusalem with great splendor.
This book has contained the history of the later years of Herod the Great, his domestic troubles, the execution of his sons, his final illness, and the division of his kingdom after his death.

