In the twentieth year of Artaxerxes, Nehemiah came to Jerusalem and inspected the ruined walls by night. He then rallied the people to rebuild them, saying, “Let us rise up and build,” and they strengthened their hands for the good work.
This book has contained the history from the first year of Cyrus king of Persia, who allowed the Jews to return and rebuild the Temple, through the reigns of Darius, Xerxes, and Artaxerxes, until the times of Ezra and Nehemiah.

